tradestock.model.portfolio

Class Portfolio

  • java.lang.Object
    • tradestock.model.portfolio.Portfolio
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPortfolio

    public class Portfolio
extends java.lang.Object
implements IPortfolio
    This class represent a Portfolio implements IPortfolio. A portfolio of stocks is simply a collection of stocks (e.g. 10 shares of company X, 10 shares of company Y, etc.). A portfolio object could get portfolio name, get total stocks number, get stocks number at certain date, get stocks cost, get stocks cost at certain date, get total value of stocks, get total value at certain date, add a transaction record, and get portfolio state as string.

      • addTransaction

        public void addTransaction(java.lang.String stockSymbol,
                           java.time.LocalDate date,
                           boolean isSell,
                           double number)
        Add a transaction history of stocks in this portfolio. If stock symbol is null or empty string, or date is null, or number is not positive. When selling stocks, if number of stocks is bigger than current stock number, this method will throw IllegalStateException.
        Specified by:
        addTransaction in interface IPortfolio
        Parameters:
        stockSymbol - given stock symbol to add transaction record
        date - given date of transaction
        isSell - true if sell, or false if buy
        number - number of stocks to operate
